@startuml Workflow One Sequence Diagram
title DormDash Workflow One - Employee enters new inventory

actor Employee
participant "Main UI" as UI
participant "InventoryController" as IC
participant "InventoryDataProvider" as IDP
database "MySQL Database" as DB

Employee -> UI : Select "Enter New Inventory"

UI -> IC : addInventoryInteractive(scanner)

IC -> Employee : Prompt for item name
Employee -> IC : Enter item name

IC -> Employee : Prompt for category
Employee -> IC : Enter category

IC -> Employee : Validate category (loop until valid)

IC -> Employee : Prompt for quantity
Employee -> IC : Enter quantity

IC -> Employee : Validate quantity (loop until valid)

IC -> Employee : Prompt for price
Employee -> IC : Enter price

IC -> Employee : Validate price (loop until valid)

IC -> IDP : addOrUpdateItem(name, category, quantity, price)

IDP -> DB : INSERT or UPDATE inventory_items

DB --> IDP : Success / Failure result

IDP --> IC : Confirmation

IC --> UI : "Inventory updated successfully!"

UI --> Employee : Display success message

@enduml